<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="920" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d920">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-22"><hi rend="italic">November 22,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root informs Mr. Meyer that many influential Hebrews in this country
                            are endeavoring to raise relief funds, being greatly distressed over the
                            reports of Jewish loss of life and suffering in the recent outbreaks.
                            Requests him to furnish as accurate report of these occurrences as
                            possible, giving the number of killed, wounded, sick, and destitute, and
                            the losses sustained.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>